         <listPlace>
            <t:place type="church dabr" subtype="institution">
               <t:placeName>ʾƎndāmosā Dabra Salām Mazgaba Śǝllāse</t:placeName>
               <t:placeName type="alt">ʾƎndāmosā Mazgaba Śǝllāse</t:placeName>
               <t:country ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3010Ethiop">ʾItyoṗyā</t:country>
               <region notBefore="1991" type="RegionalState" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5932Tegray">Bǝḥerāwi Kǝllǝlāwi Mangǝśti Tǝgrāy</region>
               <t:settlement from="2014-02-04" to="2014-02-05" type="warada" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC6520Irob">ኢሮብ፡</t:settlement> 
               
               <t:settlement from="2014-02-04" to="2014-02-05" type="tabiya" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7271Endamosa ">ʾƎndāmosā</t:settlement> 
               
               <t:settlement from="2014-02-04" to="2014-02-05" type="qushat" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7272Awado ">ʾAwādo</t:settlement> 
               
               <t:location>
                  <t:geo>14.419645 39.512306</t:geo>
                  <t:height unit="m">2545.0</t:height>
               </t:location>
               <t:note>
                  <t:date type="foundation" notBefore="1700" notAfter="1800">1700-1800</t:date>
                  <t:desc type="foundation">The church might have existed at the site before the 17th cent. <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6951Mazgaba">Mazgaba Śǝllāse</t:persName>, the 17th-18th-cent. head of the monastery of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0005Gund">Gunda Gunde</t:placeName>. 
                     The place of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7272Awado">ʿAwādo</t:placeName>, where <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6951Mazgaba">Mazgaba Śǝllāse</t:persName> is said to have been born (also according to <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4781GadlaMS">his Vita</t:ref>), is located nearby.</t:desc>
                  <t:ab type="history">Dabr. The recent church building stands near the old one, which is intact. The old church of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7273Gababinno">Gababinno Mikāʾel</t:placeName> is located in the vicinity (probably an old rock-hewn structure, but the books are recent). 
                     <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0005Gund">Gunda Gunde</t:placeName> is said to be not very far (some 5 hour distance walk).
</t:ab>
                  <t:ab type="description">22 Mss. photographed: <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems001">EMS-001</t:ref> “Missal”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems002">EMS-002</t:ref> “Miracles of Mary; Miracles of Jesus¸Miracels of Michael¸Miracles of the Saviour of the World”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems003">EMS-003</t:ref> “Missal”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems004">EMS-004</t:ref> “Gädlä Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus (fols.3ra-68vb);  Täʾamrä Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus (fols. 69ra-91ra)(<t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ES92ra117">92ra-117</t:ref>rb)”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems005">EMS-005</t:ref> “Homiliary for the feasts of St. Michael ”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems006">EMS-006</t:ref> “Homily on the Sabbath of Christians; Book of the letter (from Heaven)”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems007">EMS-007</t:ref> “Vita of Mäzgäbä Śellase”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems008">EMS-008</t:ref> “Image of Raguʾel”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems009">EMS-009</t:ref> “The Hope of Praise”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems010">EMS-010</t:ref> “Sägogawa Maryam (fols.2r-20r); Mälkǝʾa Täklä Haymanot (fols. 24r-38r)”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems011">EMS-011</t:ref> “Mahǝletä ṣǝgge (fols. 1ra-43rb); Mälkǝʾa Pawlos wä-Petros (fols. 43rb-54ra); Mälkǝʾa Kiros (fols. 54ra-56va)”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems012">EMS-012</t:ref> “Book of the Funeral Rite”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems013">EMS-013</t:ref> “Story of Mary”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems014">EMS-014</t:ref> “Prayer of St. Mary on Bartas (fols. 2r-37v); Prayer of St. Qopros (fols. 39r-57v); Psalm 118 (fols. 58r-70v); Prayer of Mary to Christos (fols. 71r-73r); Gate of light (fols. 73v-81v); Song of Songs (fols. 82r-91r); Prayer of Jesus Christ (fols. 91v-95r)”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems015">EMS-015</t:ref> “Lectionary”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems016">EMS-016</t:ref> “Gospel of John”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems017">EMS-017</t:ref> “Book of the Feast of Christ's Baptism”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems018">EMS-018</t:ref> “Mǝʿraf (fols. 4ra-14rb); Dǝggwa (fols. 15ra-50rb) (Wazenna); Kǝstät zä-ʾaryam (fols.53ra)-62rb)”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems019">EMS-019</t:ref> “Vite of Giyorgis; Miracles of  Giyorgis”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems020">EMS-020</t:ref> “Yä-ḥǝmamat sälamta (fols. 1ra-14ra); Salam-prayer to Giorgis (fols. 15ra-16vb); Zǝmmare (fols. 17ra-26rb); Mäwaśǝʾt (fols. 27ra-48ra); Zǝmmare for säne (fols. 49ra-56va); Mäṣḥafä ḥassab (Computers) (fols. 57v-64v)”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems021">EMS-021</t:ref> “Vite of Mäzgäba Sǝllare; Miracles of Mäzgäba Sǝllare; Image of Mäzgäba Sǝllare; Salutation to Mäzgäba Sǝllare”; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESems022">EMS-022</t:ref> “Four Gospels”.</t:ab>
          
